# Font binaries: never touch these. Git usually detects them as binary on its own,
# but a checkout with core.autocrlf=true would silently rewrite any byte pair that
# looks like a line ending, and a corrupted .ttf fails at *render* time — the app
# just quietly falls back to a system face, exactly the bug the fonts were added to
# fix. Being explicit costs nothing.
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.png binary
*.wav binary
